	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One possible reason why Castlevania 3 used the MMC5 is because the VRC6 (used in 悪魔城伝説 a.k.a. akuden a.k.a. CV3j) used a rather odd bank switching layout (16KB bank at 8000-BFFF, 8KB bank at C000-DFFF, last 8KB hardwired at E000-FFFF) which only the MMC5 was capable of reproducing (no other Nintendo mappers have 24KB worth of swappable banks; MMC1, MMC4, and MMC3/MMC6 have only 16KB worth).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


